More than 24,000 migrants arrived in Italy from Libya in the first three months of this year - up from 18,000 over the same period in 2016. As a record 181,000 reached the Italian coast in 2016, at least 90 per cent of them have been revealed to be from Libya.

GETTY Libya's PM attacked the EU for failing to tackle the migrant crisis
